text:
There is a natural right to perceive things as you will, but only a pseudo-liberal (and thus ultimately unenforceable) right to be perceived as you will. 
This is a distinction of great contemporary relevance.
The US (and China) supported the remnants of the Pol Pot regime to frustrate the Vietnamese, though, which doesn't look so great in retrospect.
Pseudo-liberalism: "All your doors of perception are belong to us!"
"You've no right to think I'm a freak!" will still be with us, sadly.
To think Deep Angelic Reality was "fundamentally anti-human" would be a kind of absurd species narcissism, IMHO.
For how long will the token cis-female in third place be tolerated?
Guy's trying to start a race war.
You can't talk about people like that!
